**Abstract:**
This draft essay examines the cultural revolution in medieval Europe caused by the introduction of Aristotle's works in the 12th-13th centuries. It explores how the irruption of Aristotelian philosophy created a sharp awareness of the difference between faith and reason, leading to the emergence of philosophy as a separate discipline. The document analyzes the controversy among theologians about accommodating theology to Aristotelian scientific standards, particularly the model of knowledge found in the Posterior Analytics.

**AI Recommendation:** Important working draft on faith and reason; connects to broader Chantilly project materials.

